<br>
For High Elf mages, as soon as u hit lvl 4 buy ur new spells and head to orc hill. Get a group together like 3 or 4 ppl. Then just get someone to pull from the 3 pop orc camp. Sit on the path to orc hill and rest. The puller can pull wanderings and stuff there and it's always possible to run to guards whenever u need help. U will hit lvl 5 in about 1-2 hours. Now if u still have ur group get them up the orc &quot;hill&quot;. It's surrounded by orc camps and u can pull from anywhere. If ur group has alrdy disbanded get a cleric or a pally and head to the small orc camp between the path to cb and orc hill. It's another 3 pop camp. u might find some orc pawns but dont kill them. Kill the centurions and rest. Wait for them to spawn again, kill and rest. If an orc pawn spawns dont kill it. So u will have a 1 pop camp. U can try soloing it if ur partner logs off. If u get bored u can always pull the wanderers. In about 2-3 hours u will hit lvl 7 if ure doing it right. Now go on the orc hill and try pulling like crazy. I mean CRAZY. Pull every orc u see. In around 3 hours u will hit lvl 8. At lvl 8 u might want to get ur new spells and solo orc hill for a bit. Took me 3 hours to get to lvl 9 from lvl 8 on orc hill. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><table border="0">
